\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11744959 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could you tell me where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 In Chelsea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 1898. There were two of us. I mean - I - I've got a twin brother. Ten minutes older than I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How long did you live in that house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelsea{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I shouldn't think very long, I don't remember much about that, then we moved to a - a house in Thornt
on Heath. That's down - Surry, near Croydon. And - I should think there - we were there - 'til about 1906. And then we moved to a house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Upper Norwood{\*\xmlclose}
, bigger house - there were five - brothers and sisters altogether. Mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Upper Norwood{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Upper Norwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What happened after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh well then after that - in 1910 my mother died, and then - 1911 - we moved to Streatham - near an aunt who was able to look after - or keep an eye on us you see and look after us as
 children, and then - later on - I went to live with the aunt, and my - father, his - business - I think that collapsed and he had to - find somewhere else - to live you see and - and - sort of - all the family parted. The brothers and that. One brother w
e
nt to live with a friend at - some friends - at - now - yes, Fulham that's right, Fulham, and - oh this was just before I went to live - live with the aunt, because I went to stay with a - a friend in - Thornton Heath, or between Thornton Heath and - and 
-
 Nor - Upper Norwood you see - and I stayed - I suppose for some - six or eight months, and then I went to - my father was able to get another little home together, and - my brothers came back - into that home and then I went to live with this aunt you se
e, at Streatham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How long did you live with the aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
With the aunt? From 19 - 12 - 1914 'til 19 - 19. And then I left there you see and then I went into digs, and from that time onwards I was - sort of on my own in digs. First at - Clapham. And then I went down to live at Woolwich.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So we really ought to talk about two households?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 The one before your mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Afterwards, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You say there were five of you altogether in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. I had - an older sister and an older brother. Then we two twin - we two, and then a younger brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you know what year your father was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He was born in 1870 and died in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh - I don't exactly know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was he a Londoner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I think it was more in the country, somewhere round - no, I really wouldn't like to say actually where he came from. No, I was thinking perhaps he might have gone - come from Buckinghamshire
, but I don't think it was. I know he was in the marines first. He went into the marines. He had six brothers. And one sister. And all those six brothers died before they were fifty, but the one sister lived until she was eighty - for - 'til she was eight
y-one. So - it looks as though the - female are - females are the stronger - sex - stronger people on our - in our family, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did he do after being in the marines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was after that when he was a hot water fitter. Hot water engineer or fitter I think they call them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He was an employee I think you told me wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Employee. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It wasn't his own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you say a moment ago that something went wrong actually with the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh one of - yes, something in the business I think it would collapsed and - sort of he was out of work, and then he had to, you know - just after my mother died, and then he had to sell up all the stuff - all the home at - from Norwood, and that's when we
 went separated into - var - we - with various friends. And then later on he apparently got another job you see and was able to get - a little place at Streatham then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 The same kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, same kind of job, yes, 'cos he used to be with -
 Bobbies, you know, the big - no, not with Bobbies, he used to do a lot of work for Bobbies, now who was we - he with? Oh no, I can't remember who - used to be with. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember what happened when he couldn't get work, actually what happened, 
the home completely split up and you were really supported by other members of the family were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well these friends kept us you see. My brother as I say went to Fulham and I was at - Thornton Heath with friends then and they kept us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You weren't able to get any kind of assistance of any sort at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh not that I know of, no, there wouldn't be any then would there. No, no assistance or - or anything like that, it was just the goodness of friends like that. Family friends that had been, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Your mother, how old was she, when would she have been born do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well - she died in 1910, and - I think she was forty-five when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you know where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, somewhere in the country. Now I do know she came from the country somewhere. Probably it might have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 Buckinghamshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  that she sort of - round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she ever work before or after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That - well I expect she went to service I think before she was married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But afterwards she didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well she had a family, the home to keep you see, and I - yes, I know she was at home then. I don't ever - did any - not while we were growing up. Oh no, those were the days when - mothers kept at home, looked after the family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think we'd better talk about the years 1906 to 10.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Can you describe the house to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, it was - a - terraced house - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Upper Norwood{\*\xmlclose}
, it was a - beg - just beginning to be - built up then those places were. I
t was a six roomed house. The front room, then a room behind that, then there was a - a long passage, then you came to the - what - living room and a - kitchenette off that. And then more pa - and then - you carried on this passage and there was another r
o
om at the end of that. And then upstairs there was the - front bedroom, a bedroom next to it. Then there was the - a - bathroom, and then another room at the - no, not a bathroom a - a toilet it was, and then there was a small bedroom and then another sma
ll bedroom at the end, so there's about - four bedrooms upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Very roomy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It was really in those days of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you use the whole of the downstairs as living rooms, nobody slept down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not much in the - not much in the fr
ont room. But the back room - by the kitchenette you see - that was our living room and - Sundays very often or - or - Saturdays and Sundays we'd use the end room. Or when we'd finished a meal perhaps Sunday likely we'd go down to the other room. And perh
aps have meals down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You sometimes did eat meals in the front room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not the front room. Not the front room, no, the - that would be the back - right the back of the house. The end of the passage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That's further on than the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. There was the - the front room here, then you came down, then there was a - a living room there and the kitchenette off - went off that, then the passage came down here - and there was another room here, we used to call this the morning room m
ainly you see. But the - kitchen - very much like Mrs Dawson's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What was the front room used for then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well that was the - you know, holy of holies like - Sundays perhaps, Sunday evenings we might go in there and - have our hymns, and - I
 think we had a harmonium or something like that, and we'd - sing hymns round the - round the - piano or - the harmonium like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was never any other relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No, no, we never had a - only for a short time we had an aunt there but she wasn't there for long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You could put relatives up if they came to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh if we - yes, if they had come, yes. Sometimes I know my - my uncle - came home once - they were in the - Hussars, two uncles I had - in Hussars, and they c
ame home, I can remem - just remember them coming home you see, and - in this room by the kitchenette was one - you know, very high mantelpiece, and my mother was short, and she was - up on a chair dusting up there, and - one of my uncles - was home on - 
leave, or came in to see us you know and he - I can see it now, he came in and he - took my mother round the waist and - took her down and swirled her round you know. I can - you know, see it very very - plainly like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You say there wasn't a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we'd have the bath downstairs, it was - I - there was a toilet upstairs, not a bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You bought a bath into the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right, yes, we - of course in this room there was a big - kitchen range you see, a big black k
itchen range. In fact once - when my mother was ill - the winter that she was ill, 1910, it was a very wet and - and bad winter and our road where were you see hadn't been made up. And - of course we used to - have - wear boots for the wintertime, and we'
d
 come down the road, and - my boots were very muddy and I put them up on the rack - as - you know, we always had to take our - boots off when you get - put them up on the rack and I didn't know but - and one fell - there was a pot underneath - sort of thi
ng, and my boot fell into the - it was marmalade being - cooked, so - anyway it was taken out and washed off you see. I don't suppose it hurt the - any rate, we're still alive after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was it a sort of weekly bath then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. Friday nights I think, Friday nights - was our - usually our - if not Friday it would have to be Saturday you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about washday, was there a washday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Washday I expect - washdays was Monday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't send any of it out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 O
h no, no. No. No, my mother did it all, never went out to any woman like that. And of course there weren't any - washing - facilities otherwise, no shops or anything like that or - houses. No, she did it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So she didn't have any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. She was real hard working woman and - up early in the morning I know she was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was she up first then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, she was always up. Very often my father had to go away too for - his - work. You see, if he work
 - was working for a firm and that - now he did a lot of work for the - at the zoo, so of course that meant that he was away - got some rooms or something in London, or he might go down to - you know, any of the counties. I know he did a lot of work at on
e time for Bobbies at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Margate{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, so that - he was down there for - months you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There were quite long periods when you didn't see him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, like that, probably, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about the clothes, the family's clothes, were they made or mended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well they were sort of handed down from my sister, I used to have hers and - my - younger brother used to - twin brother used to have the other one's, and - you know we didn't have many new clothes. And I think if anyone were able to give - m
y mother a coat or anything like that - I can't remember whether she altered it or whether she had it altered you know, a neighbour would - probably do it for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she mend the things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Yes. She mended the things and 
every night we knelt at her - knelt - by the fire and she sat in the chair and we all said our prayers, with her - before we went to bed. And they always came up to bed to - after we were in bed they always came up and said goodnight to us again. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What time would you have to go to bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I should think about - see - oh round about - it'd be - seven or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. 'Cos we were only - young then, 'course as - as - when we were younger I mean I know we'd - probably about six o'clock we'd
 go you see. And - summer I suppose would be a little later.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you share a bed with the sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, I shared the bed with my sister. Quite a time like and then - I - un - until she went - started business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Shoes, were they bought readymade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, yes, they would be, yes. Of if - if they weren't bought you know like if anybody - or boots, we - I don't think we went into shoes. It was practically always boots we had. And I know the time when I've had - if my shoes were no
t - mended - I've had to wear my brother's boots, if he'd got a spare pair like that. My father used to do a lot of - mending too, when he was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When he was home would he help in the house in other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 ways}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, I think he used to help in the h
ouse. Not a lot of course, I mean but - I know he used to - he was decorating the house. And - he - in this house at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Norwood{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 he put in - pipes you see, hot water pipes and a radiator. 'Cos I always remember that, 'cos it was all painted - gold you see and 
- I think we were about the only house there probably in the street that had - got such a thing I think in those days. Yes. I do remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would he ever do any cooking or cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well - he - I think he used to do some cleaning, but I don'
t remember him doing any cooking. But cleaning and that I know we used - and he'd see that we did our work properly like - my brothers had the boots to clean and the knives and - there was no - slipshod work in that, if they weren't done properly then you
'
d do it again. And I had my jobs of dusting to do. And - sometimes - we - if we went out with the school, you see, it would only be Saturday mornings, never in the week we didn't go out like today, and if we went out Saturday mornings - with anything like
 that you see - we'd have to do our work when we came back. We couldn't - you know, say well you were out - somebody else do it. No, we had to carry on and - and forego our - pleasure in the afternoon you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Dusting was your main job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Dusting, 
yes, dusting. Dusting, that's right. Yes. And holiday times was al - holiday times was always a great day - great time, we always used to take - undo the pin cushions, and get out all the pins and that had - or needles mainly of course that had - gone rig
h
t through. That was always an exciting job. And another job we had - did when we were - school - holidays - was to - undo a - a horsehair mattress, you know. Pull it all apart. Put it all back again and then it would be a bit softer to - lay on then after
 that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well he might tell us some stories - some - sometimes he used to make - make them up I mean and we'd sit on the - sit on his lap perhaps and - be in fits of laughter over some things he'd - tell us 
and - he'd always make up a name of something like that, now - oh dad, daddy, what's that and that, and they - oh, that's what you call a - some ridiculous name he'd made up. But any rate it was all fun you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about looking after you if your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I suppose really we were old enough then to - to more or less be left on our own like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would he ever take one of the children out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, we used to go out walks, oh yes, he used to take us out and Su
ndays we always used to - Sunday afternoon or evening we'd go for a walk if we had - didn't go to church. And - times were you know we were sent to church in the afternoon and I remember once particularly, we - we didn't want to go so we went off - down i
n
 the - into the - park, and - then of course we worked our way out to the church, but on the way up, my mother and father and - they had decided to take the baby out and of course we walked straight into them. We couldn't help ourselves. They'd taken a - 
a
 - different route round you see and we thought well our daddy never comes round this way and that, they always got up - the main road and Church Road and that but - ran into us so of course we were naughty children. I think we went to bed, we all had to 
go up to bed - up to our rooms for - for a long time without any tea. That Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would that be the usual way if they disapproved of what you'd done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, very often we were sent up to our room. Sometimes without our tea. And - we might have 
a - a little supper brought up to us. So we had to go to bed too. You see, not just - not only just sent to our room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They didn't believe in physical punishment then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh we did have that, yes, at times we did have it, yes. Oh I 'don't mind admit
ting it, and I - I'm none the worse for it. That's why I say today they don't get any thing. Which I think would do some of them good. Have a little discipline. Well they were - they're not hard. But - they would have obedience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of things do you feel then that they thought were most important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well, to be honest. To tell the truth you see. If you thought you could get out of it, and, you know, tell a little lie or something like that - you - they'd find out you see and then of 
course we'd get - be punished. Oh no, they wouldn't have any - they wouldn't have any - lies. Like that, 'cos naturally you think - sometimes think you can - you know, you say, no, you didn't do a thing, but eventually you did. They found out and you had 
to - you know - confess you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you find them both, your mother and your father, easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I think we could talk to our mother - probably more easily than our father then because of course he was - sort of away quite a bit. And p
ossible those day - years you see, and - and then - not exactly a stranger but of course you wouldn't bear quite the same - attitude as you might say. And of course in the - naturally too we were brought up, you know, children must be seen and not heard t
o a certain extent. And - yes, well I - I think we could talk to our mother better, 'cos, as I say, she was with us all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 She was the more influential really on the whole you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And no talking when grown ups were talking then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh no, no. No. And no talking - not a lot of talking at mealtimes either. I remember one - one Sunday - when we were having our - dinner in the - far - far room you see, and - I think we all got a - bit of a laughing fit on or something, but 
any rate - my father - oh my mother had made this - you know, currant - the long currant pudding. Plum duff you see. And - I think - may have told you this before of course - you know - when my father came round the table, now who likes the end piece? Who
 
likes the end? Well - no, do you like the end? No. My - brother didn't like it, my sister didn't like it. And - my young - my twin brother, he didn't like it, I didn't like it. And of course the little boy - the younger brother, I suppose he wasn't asked.
 
Very well mother, he said, none of them like it so just cut it in two - gave a piece, half to mother you see and half to himself on his plate there you see, and - we were all practically in tears 'cos we had no - no afters you see. Well nobody liked it yo
u see. So after that of course we - nobody ever - we none of us ever said that we didn't like the end. It was cut in sort of in the pieces and you had it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You were expected to just eat what you were given really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, more or less, yes, y
es. I couldn't stand parsnips, I think parsnips must have been - well, we had a - this house had a long garden and my father - grew - a lot of veg - vegetables and that and I suppose parsnips were easy, and - I - presume we were served up with a lot of pa
r
snips and that, I - I detested the things. But - any rate - I mean, well, if you didn't have them then you were - came up the next day for your dinner. So I suppose I eventually somehow pushed it down. And then I - suppose I went years without them, but I
 like parsnips now. Either baked or boiled.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What other vegetables would he grow then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh cabbages. I know cabbages and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Potatoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, I think he grew potatoes too, there wouldn't be - don't think there'd be much else. 'Cos they 
didn't have - we didn't have tomatoes then, well I know we kept chickens too. Yes. Because - one - Christmas - we went over to - Streatham to this aunt's, this was before mother died, for Christmas, and - opening a bottle of - wine, I don't know - I - don
'
t remember what wine it was, but - the - you know, it popped out and went all over the veg - into the vegetable dishes, vegetable dishes were - on the table - just as we were serving dinner, auntie was serving dinner, and this all - you know - fumed out a
n
d over onto the vegetables. Well it happened there was - some outside, some more outside so those got taken out - and - any rate they weren't wasted, I suppose mother took them home - gave them to the chickens. And of course the next day they - well - or 
a late - a little later on they were all - rolling about, these chickens. Drunk. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there any fruit in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, there were apple trees, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So you didn't have to buy vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think - no,
 we couldn't have done that, no, and a lot of people all the way round there grew you see and they were always giving - giving things - to one like that, same as they do today really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could you describe a typical day's meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, I suppose so. 
Used to have - porridge in the morning as far as I can remember porridge for breakfast. And - oh I suppose really - we had quite a lot of - must have been salt beef I suppose, boiled beef and carrots. I know sometimes it was very salty, whatever we had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That's for dinner you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Din - for dinner, yes. Sundays I know we used to take it in turns to have a - a - you know, one - one week - one would have the - half an egg in the egg cup, the other would have it on their bread, and - reversed the following week you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That's for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 For break - Sunday breakfast, yes. And - mainly - I suppose bread and butter and jam. Or dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, that would - bread and butter and jam would be for tea. But - 
morning would be - porridge and then - I suppose bread and - dripping. Because in those days of course you got a lovely - a good beef, with nice fat on it, and really lovely dripping. Beef dripping. Everybody talks about those days don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How often would you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh I - more or less I should think only the weekends really. Sausages I think we used to have too. Well we'd have a - you know, half a sausage really with - mainly as I say vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Fish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't ever recollect having fish. I don't recollect fish - for dinner. Or - or a meal like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have any tinned food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not that I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Corned beef? No, no, I don't think that was - know - known in those days. Sure it
 wasn't. No, we didn't have anything of that. Beef, as I say, mainly beef I think really because - when I was a youngster, I don't know how - my mother had to go - used to have to go to Mill Hill - to see somebody - granny I think it was, the granny, and 
- that was - we always used - to have to take - beef - sandwiches for dinner that day to school and I - I loathed them. You know. Dry - beef and that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I daresay we had some rabbit, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would that be from butchers or did people come round selling it from door to door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I should think that would be from the butchers really. Yes. 'Cos we hadn't got a lot of open ground there, not round about to go and catch - rabbits.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No. No. We always used to go down to the - down to the bakers, I remember that, go walk - going down to the bakers - and - you know, you put the loaf on and then it was weighed, and then there's always a little bit of makeweight you see, always put a
 - a little bit cut - off a - corner or crust of a bread - another loaf to make - make up the proper weight. And then - and coburg loaves, those are the ones - the round ones with like four corners, I often used to take hold of that with just one corner, 
of course it would come off - I had to eat that of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
I don't think she made - and yet somehow I - well she made marmalade, yes. I know she made marmalade but I don't - don't recollect actually the jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Pickles - no, I don't think we - she made pickles. 'Cos you didn't have much in those - then, the - little ones like that, not like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I know they made - they did - make some wine because - she had made - they had
 made parsnip wine, and the - year mother died you see then we had to - as I say - father had to sell up all and that, and - all - lot of this parsnip had to go down the drain. Because - well people round about didn't seem to care for it and - and that wa
s that, he couldn't take - carry it about with him or anything. So that went down the drain, I don't think we had much of that. I suppose you might have had a little sip at Christmas time, a small drink, but not - generally of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And they didn't make beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about home made medicines, did she make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well she didn't make them but I - well except that - you know - oh a jar of - of - jug of - licorice wasn't it they used to make a - a jug of licorice. Had that when you got colds or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
One thing I remember is where - at Christmas times and that, and even some Sundays in the winter, but Christmas time especially, we used to have the open fire and the - joint was done on the spit, turned so many times bac
k - you know - and that's the way it was cooked. Mm. And another thing I remember my mother used to have - I don't know if it was Guinness actually, I didn't know much about it then, but I know she used to put the poker in the fire, when it was hot put it
 into the - tumbler of - wine - beer or - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 Guinness}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 , whatever it was, to warm it, I suppose to take the - yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was it a range then with a fire in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes, that's right, yes, be a black range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No gas cookers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I suppose we had gas in the - outside you see for cooking. But quite a lot was done on the range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You did have a gas cooker as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think the - I think we had - yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You would do the kind of quick meals on the cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I suppose they were, yes, and - any - stews and soups and that were always - done on the range of course for two or three days like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So she did soups and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, we used to have - well, with the bones you see, they used to do bone - get the bones and - st
ew up like that and - take the fat off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would it be a kind of regular Sunday hot joint and then Monday cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Monday cold and then - yes, and then - done up one way the next and perhaps then on the - towards the end of the week - we'd have - some
thing else - some more bones perhaps and - a - just soup and bread, perhaps for Friday, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you feel that your mother was having sort of less food so that the rest of you could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I don't seem to remember that. I think we were all served the same really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When your father was actually at home he was there for all the meals was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, he'd be home the weekend then you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But he wouldn't come in for dinner {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} no, no. No, he used to take sandwiches, if he was - working in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 like that or - came home - at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you see him at all then, would he be away before you were having breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, he'd - yes, anything like that. 
And - and we'd be in bed before - yes probably in bed before he came home. Especially sort of winter times when it was dark. He always used to come up and see us and then we used to call out to him, hello dad, you home, or something like that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He always came up to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, he always came up to see us if - when he came home, if we were in bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You all sort of sat round the table then, when you were having a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had your own chairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you always sit in the same chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Same - always in the same place, yes. Mm. Mother one end and the - father the other end you see, and then the - two boys one side and - or - yes, and - the other - smaller boy and myself one side you see, if my sister wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Even the youngest would be at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 At the table, yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not allowed to talk too much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no, we were not allowed to talk a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You could talk a bit though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, yes. And if w
e - you know, if there were things not right or anything or if we talked too much there'd be - a cane or - a ruler or something we'd - get a tap like that. You know, we were - reprimanded if we'd - didn't obey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they make you sort of sit up straight on your chairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, Yes. Yes, sit up to the table and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Hold your knife and fork the right way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You could ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could you bring anything to the table, like a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no, were never allowed to read at table, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember anything else about the manners at table that they insisted on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I know once when we - as - once we were all laughing, another thing that one - Sunday I think it wa
s we were - something, we were all laughing - outside, that was the first one went out, of course that made us laugh, the second one out after a little bit, outside, and we - until all the five children were outside. Outside the door you see. And my broth
e
r - he opened the door, very quietly and - and looked in, there was mother and father sitting there laughing you see. And the door - you see, then the - in shutting the door - I suppose pulling - going to shut the door you see, he - must have made a - a l
i
ttle more noise you see. My father called out - what are you doing to the door? Come inside, you see, so he had to go inside, and - say what he'd been doing you see. And - any rate, was told to go outside again, we were out there for another five minutes 
or so. Can you behave yourselves now? Yes, dad, we - yes. You sure? Yes daddy, yes. Well you can come in now, so we all - trouped in, sat down, almost tearful like you know having been kept outside, and carried on our meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you all have to wait until everybody had finished and then leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, before we got down, yes, and always had to ask before we got - always said grace before we'd to - before we started a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not at the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I think we said - beginning and the
 end. Yes. For - for a time like you know, while we're young, like that. And gradually left it off. Afraid I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your mother serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would she put it on your plates or would she bring the dishes and put them on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I think - sometimes in the week it was served - from the - from the - onto the plate, but weekends you see when we had more time to sit down and - have it it was served from the vegetable dishes. And always the covers on you see. Put on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If you wanted something on the table you just asked for it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes. Please pass the - jam or - or may I have - may I have so and so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What if you left food uneaten, that was produced again was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well it - not - it just depen
ded whether we - I suppose really - why we'd left it, if it was a bit too much for us you see, well we wouldn't have to - sort of - eat it again, but if it was anything that - sort of cabbage and that like that we said we didn't like and that, yes, yes. W
ell - have it the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What kind of people do you think that your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well - now let me see. I should think just good - honest children. Honest people you see, we'd been brought up - to tell the truth. I ca
n't say that - I remember much more, not so much about to - well possibly they thought we'll help - help somebody, but I don't suppose that was really - part of our bringing up. We used to have to help I mean, not to - be unkind to people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If another child hurt you did they say you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well it just depended I think - with the boys more really. If they were - you know really nasty and that well you must stand up for yourself. Like that really, I think that was the - their idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about among you brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh we used to have our little - just general squabbles and that but otherwise we got on - well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they say very much about that sort of thing, on how you should behave to your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well no, I can't re - can't recollect really. We were sort of a happy family together I suppose, it was not necessary maybe. As we all - helped each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If there was something that you were worried about yourself would you keep it to yourself or would you tell your mother or father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well - personally I think I'd probably used to keep it to myself for a time until she knew there was - something, but - act - at the same time I can't actually recollect - of anything - being like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I wondered whether you felt it was sort of easier if there was something upsetting you to just go along and tell your mother about it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, I - no, I don't think - no, I don't think she was distant like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you say that she found it easy to show affection to her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well she - yes, she did to us. Well I say - as I say, sometimes we were naughty and perhaps didn't deserve it but I always remember - feeling that - you know, that she did love us, in spite of s
ometimes us being a bit naughty and that which is - more or less only natural. But - use, we always got - all - all got our goodnight kiss, as well, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Can you tell me about a birthday, what would happen when you had a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Birthday, oh. 
I don't think - there was much, I think - I think we did have a - not very often, but I think we did have a - I had a schoolfriend in. And I suppose my brother had somebody in as well with ours being the two - the same day you see, although that's - after
 Christmas you see, so that - our Christmas presents and - pleasure really was all - together. But it's more likely I'd have somebody - in in the summertime, to come in and play and then to stay and have tea. Rather than the wintertime. Then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What would happen at Christmas then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How do you mean? Our Christmases?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have a big meal in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh there was always the - a big joint of beef, was always an aitch bone there I can - I can see that thing, you know, big aitch bone going
 round and that, yes. Beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And then games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes, but not - and - we used to do charades or something like that you see. But not a lot of - of course we didn't have a lot of presents in those days. But what we had I mean to say we were - I suppose thankful for and - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have anyone to stay, like relations?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Christmastime, only - no, not - so much to stay, we'd - perhaps go over to Streatham and - was really walking distance then you see. Although - I mean it's two - ooh, 
more than two or three miles isn't it. Yes, a long way. But of course in those days there weren't the - so many buses and that. Trams rather more that that, but - I know my father and that often used to walk over. They used to go over Saturday night, Satu
r
day, or every other Saturday I think, over to - Streatham to see his sister. And as I say, and mother and father they often used to go down to - Thornton Heath clock and listen to the - political meetings, Saturday evenings you see. And then - if we were 
n
ot - if they didn't - say what time - they more or less said about what time you know, but - if they said, well if I'm late tonight, or I shall be a little later, you go to bed at - half past eight or something like that and - we'd probably hear them come
 in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your mother ever go out by herself, just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 My mother? No. No, she never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they have sort of other relatives apart from your aunt who they went to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not close at hand, no. No, they lived - some way aw
ay you see. So that - we didn't often see them. I had an aunt in - well this - no, that's right, my mother's sister. I went to stay with her - in Queen Anne's Gate. Queen Anne's Mansions, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had a holiday there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I was there for two or thre
e day - I remember - the afternoon that my aunt came down to - to take me back. It - we'd been down - she'd come down, we'd gone over to Grange Park for the afternoon, and coming back there was a thunderstorm, and - oh I should - I cried, and - I shall no
t
 be able to go out. I shall not be able to go back with auntie tonight, but any rate I did. And this was - when did I say his name was, Sir Aston Webb? Sir Aston Webb. My aunt was - apparently housekeeper to him - there, and - I remember I was - she'd tak
e
n me upstairs - to help her with the dusting one day and she said, well I must go downstairs now, and she went through a door, and that went downstairs and do you know I couldn't find that door, I didn't know where I was, and - that goes sort of - from th
e
 kitchen part, from the back of the house, kitchen area, it goes upstairs, these stairs and open a door and you come into the - the private - private part of the house - Sir Aston Webb's house, but I never found that day - door. I - and I was in tears, an
d she - I was up there so long that she eventually came to know where - where I'd got to. But - as I say I just couldn't - find it. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. That was the reason I was able to I suppose to go up and stay there, when - beca
use he was away at the time. But - and I know my father came up - to see us, to - to see me - sometime then you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What kind of a place did he have, quite large?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh, very - yes, a large - a large place and - to me it was lovely furniture and 
all that. Nice big room - I can remember this big room looking out onto the front somewhere. But - as I say I should think I was only about - probably six or seven then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He was an architect wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that your only sort of holiday or did you have other holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No - I remember having a holiday after my father had done this - work, helping with this work down at Bobbies in - Margate. We went down there for a week's holiday. But actually when it was I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did you do when you were in Margate then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
In Margate? Oh it was going down on the - playing on the sand you see. Because we were still - I suppose about - eight I suppose then. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Riding ponies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. On the donkeys there and - I remember at
 night the - there was a - there must have been the big - a battleship off - Margate - standing there, because - the Marines were in and they were - you know, we - actually we'd gone up to bed but - my mother and father had gone out and - these marines mu
st have come down the road 'cos of course we nipped out of bed and were standing at the window, in our nighties like watching them go by. So - they wouldn't - they didn't know we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So your father really was able to have a holiday at the end of the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. That time, yes. But - otherwise we didn't get many holidays I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was the only holiday as a whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That's the only one I remember really. But I do - as I say, remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you all go out for the day on a Bank Holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. 'Cos we went to the zoo once. And - yes, that was before my mother died. My brother had been given the - string bag with the food in. We got off the bus. And - our - we used to have a - a school attendance - you kno
w - used to come round the schools and - find out who was - always too many times and that - and - this man got off the bus and of course it was our school attendant. Of course wanted to know why we - and my brother had let - come down you see, the bus ha
d
 gone off and to Camden Town and he'd left the food bag on the - bus, so of course - we had to wait until the bus came back. On the return journey - some half hour probably or more - afterwards and - we got the food back and I know that, we were going to 
t
he zoo that day. Mm. Then of course our school - our Sunday school holidays and that - treats and that we used to - go into - brakes, get into brakes and go - down - somewhere near the Crystal Palace to fields down there, Gypsy Hill - as far as I can reme
mber, down some fields there. Or - in the - some other place in the - back of what was Church Road leading from Crystal Palace down, and - fields over there we used to go off into brakes there and have our - sports and suchlike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you ever go out with your parents to listen to a band or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh in the park, yes, we used to go up to the - Grange Park which was very near us. Just walking distance, and - go down there and - listen - to the bands and - see them walking around like th
is you know. As you said the monkeys parade as it was always called, yes. Yes, mostly in the Sunday time and that - Sundays we used to have that. And - in this - road that we lived - across the road there was a big field, it hadn't all been built up on th
e other side, and in the summertime, they used to have a big marquee and an open air service there every Sunday. So we probably - might go over there. Or we could - sit in the garden and - hear the hymns and that and join in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You told me about sitting round the harmonium, were there any other sort of occasions when you'd have a sing-song together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I suppose Christmas time and that we'd have a - you know - a little - get together like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would it always be hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, I don'
t think so, we used to - of course we had - we knew some songs then didn't we, not that I could rec - perhaps recollect them now. - Some of the old songs. Suppose we used to - sing. Just like - just - was it - Just a Song at Twilight. I can remember that,
 joining in little bits of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there any other musical instruments, anyone play anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No, we were not a musical family as far as that goes, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were you musical enough to sing in the choir yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I never went in the choir, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Apart from Christmas do you remember your parents playing games with you, like dominoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we might have a game of cards. Beat your Neighbour and - things like that. And - no, I don't think any - any other, ludo and - or - 
you see. Oh we had ludo and snakes and ladders. We'd play with those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there many books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Books, books. I was not much of a reader myself. My sister was the one, she'd - get hold of books from somewhere and - you know, have it up
stairs, be sitting up there reading and that, she used to read, but not - not for me. My brother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think they used to read a book - yes, I think - I seem to remember mother read - reading a book sometimes, but what 
it would be I don't know. Some of the - of - one of the - would it be Mrs - Henry? Henry? Henry Wood, yes, some of those - you know. Yes, that's right, anything like that. Those type of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they have a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Newspaper. I don't recoll
ect a newspaper. Actually. I suppose my father did bring one - one home sometimes. But not delivered, there was certainly not one delivered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not even an Sunday one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. No, we never had a Sunday paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And any sort of family magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I don't think we had any - not the family magazines. Might have had a church magazine, or something like that or - there used to be one - I was going to say, was it the Christian Herald we had perhaps. Not a - not regularly but it was - now and a
gain I suppose that - mother perhaps would pick one up or have one given to her you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you go out shopping with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, we used to go out - shopping - Saturday afternoons that would be I think, yes. Mainly Saturday aftern
oon, 'cos we had quite a way to walk to the shops you see. They were to - Thornton Heath then we'd go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was your father back on Saturdays or did he have to work Saturdays as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Some weekends he'd be - some weekends he'd have to work, but - un
less he was right away I mean he was - he was - was at home Saturdays and Sundays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't have to wait 'til Saturday night to get the Sunday joint then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well no, no, not actually, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If he was paid on the Saturday you would have had to wait but if he finished on the Friday you wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. Well I suppose really they - used to wait 'til the evening time because of course it was cheaper then to get a - a joint in the - evening because it used to be - auctioned off like. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But you didn't wait? You don't remember actually buying meat as late as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't think so, no, I don't actually - remember as late as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 On Sundays you wore different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Always - always Sunday suit - Sunday clothes, and the boys in the Sunday suits
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No. No. No, you had to sit - if you didn't go to Sunday school, which mostly we did Sunday school, and - sometimes we'd go - in the evening - to - church. And - but - o
therwise we - go either for a walk you see or else we'd - have to sit and - in the - end room like and - with a book or something like that. But not - no games were played, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you go to morning church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well Sunday school was in the afternoon, wasn't it, Sunday school in the afternoon, and then the church in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Nothing in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not at first - no, not for a long time. I don't we had - we didn't have the Sunday school in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What denomination was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Church of England. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your mother and father go or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
They used to go sometimes, not every Sunday, but - but mainly - in the autumn and the winter, but Sunday evenings - fine we used to go out for the walks. All together like
 you see. But it was more - autumn time and - winter when we might go - mother would - come to church with us, you know, take us up to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They didn't run a Band of Hope or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was a Band of Hope at the - yes, and they had a - Girls Friendly Society also
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you join that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I used to belong to the Girls Friendly Society for some years - I never - didn't go to the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did the Girls Friendly Society do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I don't know, we used to chat
 about you know and - perhaps we might have a - some prayers, and - a hymn or two. And then - you know, somebody might give us a little talk on something or sometimes it - sometimes it might be more of a - a little social - talk - really, or talk all toge
ther in a way and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was a week night was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was - yes, that was in a week night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Is there anything else that went on at the church there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't remember much about the church really, as I say only that - I know - all prize
 giving then and then we used to have our - you know, days out for the - whatsname.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember the sermons, what the sermons were about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. I know - I know at - always at Harvest time it was - oh wonderfully decorated, and great bunches of
 grapes hanging round, all round the - pulpit, and that was the boys side you see and the girls - Sunday school - girls sat this side you see, and - and of course the boys used to - where they could you know - put their hand up and - take a few. We were n
ot able to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well he used to like to - he used to go down only to the - as far as I know to go and - listen to the - meetings, down - what they called - down at the - Clock Tower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that just fore entertainment really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 More or less, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you know what his views were though,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I really couldn't say because we - we never went down to those. I know sometimes there were some - you know, quite rowdy times and things like th
at, down there, when he's - perhaps come back and I've heard him talking to - somebody that - you know - what it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You don't know what your mother's political opinions were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I haven't any idea, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did he vote actually? Did your father vote in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, I suppose he did, I really couldn't say. 'Cos we didn't have many elections then did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He could have been away of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. I - I really couldn't - I really - as I say couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He never talked politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When your father wasn't working, apart from going down to the meetings, can you think of any other sort of forms of enjoyment he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well - that was weekends, I think he was - main
ly he was too tired sort of thing and - rested and - sort of got to bed early, 'cos they were never late going to bed in those days. Really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did he belong to a club for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not that I know of. Not that I can recollect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about sick clubs, funeral clubs, you don't remember them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh - what was that one they had at home - Hearts of Oak. He belonged to the Hearts of Oak - benefit society, yes, I remember that, 'cos - Min belongs to that and - reminded me of it like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would your mother or father ever go out for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well they would have that Saturday evenings, that's all. Saturday evenings then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, when they were down - listening to the - meetings you see. They'd probably perhaps - just - c
all in and - into the - public house there and have a drink but - they wouldn't stay long. They nev - they were not one to sit in the pub. For an evenings - entertainment, he was not like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was he interested in sports of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about Derby Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Derby Day, no, I don't think we were - knew much about Derby Day much before then did we. No, I don't think he did. Not - no. Well there wasn't such a great deal on then was there. As far as then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Or football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, not football I don't think, no. Nor cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could we talk about playing games and so on as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 As a child, yes. Always skipping ropes, hoops. I can remember - in the autumn days we always - we always got our hoops out, and we
re - allowed out up 'til about say - well - about this time, it might be about - half past five, and then as the days got darker so of course it would be earlier and then - probably - after - at the end - towards the end of October we wouldn't have any ti
me out at all then. Just - after school time you see and before we had our tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You played out in the street then, you were allowed to play in the street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, you went down - yes, along the street, just in the street like that. 'Cos the - as I 
say the road - wasn't made up at first. And then later it was - made up at first. And then later it was - made up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was this a group of girls, or your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 My brothers and - yes, my brothers and the - there was a girl I used to go
 to school with - two or three doors from our - our house, and - we'd probably go out and - play like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your mother mind who you played with at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well only with the - not actually I think as - but as long as we were in the street we were not allowed to go out of the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You don't remember her saying there were some children you weren't to mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, I don't - I don't - recollect that, no. As I say I don't think there were many children there really, down the bottom
 end there might have been more but we didn't - didn't - connect with those so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she mind if you got your clothes dirty when you were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well of course it was not - not all that good was it. No. Because it meant work for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You belonged to the Girls Friendly Society, were there any other sort of clubs or youth organizations or anything you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think so, no, 'cos Band of Hope I didn't belong to. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you sot of collect anything, have any hobbies? You didn't collect birds eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I - I think my brothers went - bird nesting like but - of course it's a thing that we were told we shouldn't do, and I think that probably that was done - you know, unbeknownst as you might say, as one of the 
sidelines that they did but - went out with somebody, 'cos at the back of this house - there was the woods - a wood there you see so that - it was not so - it wasn't so hard to get in from the next street up - to go - get into these woods really and they 
- either black-berrying and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You kept hens, were there any other pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we didn't have anything else, no. No cats, no dogs. And no rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you garden yourself at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well - well - no, when we - I lived at - w
hen we lived at Thornton Heath, when I was really little, we used to have a ha'penny a week, and I used to go and plant mine in the garden. Many and many a week I'd go and plant my ha'penny, thinking it was coming up. But it never did. Oh yes, it's got le
ft there. Somebody had some finds later on. Of Queen Victoria.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you go out country walks or fishing, things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, my brothers went - you know, where was it, up on - somewhere they used to now, along Beulah Hill - they used to go tiddl
er fishing, bring them home and they'd go straight down the lavatory. Where they landed up those poor things. But - of course they were told not to do it and - if they did bring a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 jam jar}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  home that's where they went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you ever get a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No. No. I could never ride a bicycle. Wasn't 'til some years afterwards - I suppose when I was about fifteen my uncle - wanted me to have a bicycle, my cousins had bicycles, but I could never sit a bicycle, could never get on with it. So - I never had a b
icycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Any sort of sports, games of that kind, tennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I didn't used to play tennis much, no, no, I - only small - in a field perhaps with a girl I might - knock a ball about really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Nothing of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 As a girl would you have gone to any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think so, no, wouldn't have been any - concerts then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Or theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. Might go if they - if the Sunday school had a - any - sort of - show or anything like that, I should probably be allowed to go to that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember the first time you went to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Theatre? Oh yes, I was - nineteen before I first went to a theatre. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Which one did you go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I'm not sure but I - somehow I seem to think it was the Cat and - Cat and the Canar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 s one of the first ones I went to see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that in Croydon then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, that would have been in London I think. Yes. I used - no, I used to go to - when I was about - nineteen - eighteen or nineteen, I have been up to the old Vic, to see one or two there, I've seen - I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2498103\charrsid731478 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  Travatori and - I remember that was - the music then. And Carmen, that was another one I'd seen. That was about the first theatres I'd seen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember the first cinema that you saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well cine
mas we used to go to - perhaps a - Saturday afternoons, we'd pay - pay a ha'penny to sit on the front bench, and see some - or we might have a bit of - an episode of Pearl White, and then - some - comic thing you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So you went quite early to that really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was - yes, I'd be about - well as I say be about - thirteen, fourteen when I went then, to that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It was fairly early then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. That was when we were - I was at Streatham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would this cinema have been in Streatham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
In Streatham, yes, yes. That was the days when I used to have to be sent - probably be sent down to the grocers to get a bottle of whisky. Three and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Why were you sent to get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well my aunt would have sent me there - got me to go down for that you see. But that was in the days -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that for herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Ay? No, not so much for her - she used to keep in the house because - grandma used to come up you see for - and when she'd done a long walk - into - come up to t
he house - it was always a little - tot of - whisky for her. But that's the only time or if we had - if they did have visitors like that, some - gentleman might come along you see and - but - not very often, it wasn't a - not a regular thing to have out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 While we're still in Norwood.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Norwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If your mother was ill would anyone come in, any neighbours or relative come and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, you had - yes, you'd have a neighbour - would - be able to come in and - used to come in and help us
. It wasn't - often - except of course in her last illness, then of course - that was - double pneumonia - she'd contracted and - that's when - my aunt was - another - her sister like was down then. She came down and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was that rather sudden, quite a short illness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. Really, yes, yes, she'd taken my brother up to - London - to Guys Hospital you see, and it was coming back and waiting on - London Bridge station she evidently caught cold, and - this - I think she was ill for about a fortnight. A
nd - and I remember - when - after she died - I always seemed - I don't know whether I am correct but to me it always seems as though I - I - that a white sheet was al - put over that door, afterwards, and - presumably the room was fumigated. I feel sure 
I - I can remember that - sheet, of course they don't do that now, naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember when she died were there a lot of people who came in to sort of see the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, there wouldn't be a lot. We all - I know we all went up - I was at s
chool, been going to school and - it was the - beginning of December so the days were dark, and I was coming home from school I suppose about - four o'clock - something, four or half past four you see, and I could hear somebody calling, is that you Agnes?
 
Is that you Agnes? 'Cos it was so dark. And I said - yes, I'm coming. And - we had to go up and say goodnight to mother. And I can remember going in and saying goodnight to her. And then I remember - in the night when my father came in. I suppose he thoug
ht, well I - I probably was - thought to be asleep but I remember - him saying to my sister that - mother had gone. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 The funeral started from the house did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Can you remember what the funeral was like, were there a lot of people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not a lot, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Just family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That - as a matter of fact my father had got - developed pleurisy so he wasn't able to go. But - this aunt from - Streatham, she was there.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 She sort of arranged things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I suppose she did really, 'cos my father as I say, my father was ill, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You children all went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes, we went. That was at the - Streatham - cemetery at - Croydon way like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there a tea afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't think so, I don't recollect that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have to wear mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, we were in - black for - oh six months or more. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Then it just stopped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well gradually - no, you went into - I had a gray dress after that. I remember. Yes. Black then the grey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you feel that people sot of treated you with special sympathy and all that because you'd lost your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think they did, especially down at - especially at school, I remember the school, the schoolmistress was very - kind. She w
as a - a - an elderly person, very stout too, and - I remember when I went - to school and that she - she took me in and - and sat me on her lap and talked to me and - put her arms round me and kissed me, I remember that particularly. Very kind she was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you think your parents had quite a lot of friends or did they keep themselves to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think they had a lot really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they ask people in, friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I didn't have - I don't think we had many friends in really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't have people calling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, not in those days, no. 'Cos as I say we'd - sort of moved and we were not - we were not what you'd call - say well off - at all really like that but - any rate mother managed, we didn't get into debt, there 
was that, I know we were never in debt. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Can you tell me about the kind of people that did live around the district where you were in Norwood? What sort of social types were they?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 The - well I don't know that we had much did we - really, I
 remember - butcher came - I know a butcher came to - butcher boy rather. I suppose came to the door, once, you know, as I think I said before the the - snow was on the roof, and mother evidently heard this slide and she pulled him indoors - you know, and
 just missed that - load of snow coming down on his head. And we used to have winters in those days. I mean icicles - hanging from the roof like this and snow on the roof like that. But - and as I say it used to be cold but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But I mean thinking of the kind of community in Norwood? Was it a suburb with a lot of wealthy people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I - where we were, in - in - near up - near on the Beulah Hill there was some big houses there, very big houses there. Of course - Sir Willaim Trelaw lived up there. An
d - there was somebody else, but there was another big house there, I forget his name, and - that was sort of led down to Streathan Common where the big houses were but this was a new - new - houses being built, and then down - down - the road - road that
 
led down to the - into Thornton Heath, there was new school built there, well that was a better school than the school I'd previously been to. And - there - there were more houses there but the - that lane led down from better houses here and they were th
e older houses were down there you see. So they were the smaller houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Who would live in the older houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 In the older houses? Well some of the people probably more on our own standing really you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Working class, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Your father was a very skilled man wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well, to a certain extent I suppose yes, you'd call him that which is his own - because he - he - used his - brain and - I suppose and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He would have seen himself as working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When you were a child were you sort of conscious of social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I don't think so really, not then, it was only - as you got a bit older and saw you know, things perhaps how some people - girls wer
e dressed and that, they always - in - perhaps new or very nice things. Sunday clothes and that. Which ours was - sort of different from what we used during the day but - we - during the week, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But you were aware there were these sort of other wealthy people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, that's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were they people who were working in London then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh possibly they could be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was Norwood then really a suburb of London or was it more like a village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} If I can butt
 in there it was becoming a suburb, it was - it was a - Norwood was a village, surrounded by sort of - semi-country estates. And they were beginning to be split up - into building estates. Consequently you had - a sort of - in the older part of the town y
o
u'd have working class. And then you were getting - a sort of middle class. And the - the - country estate people like Sir William Trelaw and - various other people, I know there were a lot, there were a lot of big houses round there, were gradually - get
t
ing away from it - either getting further out, or going back into - the West of London, really, that was - it was in - it was a transitional period, like most of the - what are now the suburbs of London. Were - were all in a transition at that time from -
 from village to - to town sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So Sir William then was a Londoner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes. Sir William Trelaw was - head of - a big linoleum firm in - and carpet firm in Ludgate - Hill, and he was a founder of the - Trelaw childrens homes. He was a bi
g philanthropist, I think he was Lord Mayor of London at some time or other. But that was the type of people that used to live there. Then of course - it was really - toward, as you got up towards Crystal Palace you were becoming - into the - sort of what
 
we call now the stockbroker belt. Now is that - that - yes, that is - that - if you look at it that way. I mean the stockbroker belt now has gone out well say Gerrards Cross, further out of the country. Well at that time - Crystal Palace, Sydenham were al
l
 these very big houses, Gipsy Hill - people would keep their carriage and - carriage and pair, the husband would go off - in the carriage to the station, and go up to the City, he was something in the City. And then the wife would use the carriage for wha
t - visiting, dropping cards and - and then having an at home and all that sort of thing. Now those houses are all practically derelict and all split up into flats and all this sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You remember these sort of carriage people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, down - down all that - that part any rate, down Church Road to - led right straight down to the Crystal Palace, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 This Sir William, did he play the role of a squire, was he sort of at the church fete, open the church fete and all this sort of thing?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I can't actually - recollect - about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't really sort of see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You don't really feel that you had a kind of village life as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No. Oh no, it wouldn't be a village actually village life, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't feel you belonged to a kind of community in that sense, it was just part of London to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Part of London really, yes, that's right, yes, on the edges, just begin to grow up. Thorn - Thornton Heath was - quite - well built up 
in those days you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were you brought up to sort of curtsey to any of these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I was not - no. But we had to speak politely and always - good morning - good morning sir or - to the - lady always say good morning, please and thank you of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of people around there were you expected to say sir to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well perhaps the - if the - if you saw the vicar, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there certain people, like the vicar say or the doctor or somebody like that or was it more tha
t there were a lot of people whose names you didn't know, who had carriages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I should think probably doctor and the - vicar and that you see. We hardly ever saw the doctor, we didn't need him at - we were fortunate in that respect. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\}
 Generally speaking I think you could say you - usually had to say sir or ma'am to - sort of somebody that was older than yourself. Irrespective of their - sort of station in life.</}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11293469 subject2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 >
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 A schoolteacher, a schoolmaster, anything like that you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I have a feeling it may be a bit different in Woolwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} Yes. Yes, it might.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Woolwich. Yes. Yes. Woolwich was a more - built up place than what - as I say we were just beginning to come in - in - build up then betwee
n - Thornton Heath and then the Palace. Up to the Crystal Palace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there any farm labourers there where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think there are any farm labourers round about. 'Cos that would be - that farm land I think was nearer Norbury way.
 Across the fields and that there, you go - along fields and then - come to - a bit of farm land which was really at the back of - Norbury then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about sort of poorer working class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well they were down - more near the - at Thornton Heath end. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You weren't really very much conscious of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there any families that you thought of as being rough at that time, or was it all very much an area which was respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think - they w
ere - we would think of them - in a way just like that, not a - as children we wouldn't. There might have been some and that. But - I mean there was some there who were a bit ragged it's true, which we would have thought, but then of course as - probably 
as children we didn't - give it - so much thought like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
What about this notion of a real lady, or a real gentleman, was there anyone that was pointed out to you as being a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think so, no. Not living round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember seeing a policeman around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, policeman, oh yes, yes. You - saw a policeman well you'd run, more - if you were into larks. I mean the boys - and - and then - if you got a clout from a policeman I mean - you'
d know you'd done something wrong, I personally didn't of course, get one, but the boys did, I mean they used to - climb up the lamp posts, put the lights out, you see, and perhaps a policeman'd be walking round and see then or - you know, something or ot
h
er and - the next day - or a couple of days after he's coming down, say hah - he'd say to my brother perhaps - hah - saw you standing round the - you know, with so and so, and - so he'd say - perhaps the boys - my brother might say, oh yes, he - got up an
d put the light out didn't he, something like that. So he said, well, what did you do? Oh he helped him, he was joining in and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes - yes, we must have had a landlord. Who he was I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't remember ever seeing anything of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you remember any occasion on which rough music was used to express disapproval of people in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It's when in some parts of England at that time if somebody was disapproved 
of for some reason or other they used to get hold of tin cans and kettle sand go and bang them outside their house and tell them to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, I don't - no. Not down our - not down this way I don't think, no. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Before you went to school were you ever given lessons by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I - I don't - think so. We - probably had our beads and that to play with you know, to count. But I don't think we had any lessons - as - might - as they might do today with children. Before school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How old were you when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Started school? Oh I suppose I'd be five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of a school was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was the - Beulah Road - Board school I think they called that,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Boys and girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Boys and girls, yes. Mm
. Oh - not in the same class. The girls were in one portion of the - and the boys were in - a - the - a portion over there you see, a wall there. And sometimes boys came over and of course play time and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did you think about that school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I liked school. I liked school. And then after - I don't know exactly how long I was there. After that any rate I - I had been down to I think the other school - when I was in Norwood - a new school they had - built down there, I th
ink I had been down there about a year. And then - left before we left and - went over to - Streatham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What were the teachers like, you liked them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, I liked teachers, yes. And we had big classes there too. Quite big classes. A
nd - the old type school, you know, there's a - a classroom, perhaps three classrooms here, with glass partitions, and of course if you - had to stand on the back forms - forms - for singing or anything like that you see, the back row might stand on the f
orms, we could look over into the - classroom down - next to us you see, and make faces at the girls that side. And those - those girls would make faces at the girls on the other side. Three classes there like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did the teachers emphasise things like manners and so on as being very important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of things? Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, we'd - we - well of course there used to be prizes for that too. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Neatness. And 
they used to come through - go through the hall, used to have a - a - nurse or a lady come through - I forget now whether it was about once in - three or six months and - go all through your hair. And those that were - had got - trouble with their heads, 
t
hey - were sent home and - with a note and - either if it was very bad they had to stay at home until it was cured and - others, you know, but - we had - oh I think we always had a clean sheet. That's one of the things that my mother was particular about,
 every Friday night I know we - yes - you know, she always used to go through the head, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there some really poor children in the school then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well yes, and it was in a - in a - in a poorer - part of the town, of Thornton Heat you s
ee too. Yes. Oh yes, you get mixed in the school like that. I think they still do it. Well I'm not sure whether they do do it today but I have heard of - it being done - in - some schools of recent years like. But whether they - still do that or not I don
't know do it nowadays I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you feel that the teachers treated all the children the same or did they favour some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I think they favoured some. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Which ones would they favour then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I suppose those that - the - the smart ones really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did they do when children were disobedient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well you had to go outside and probably stand with your hands on your head like this for so long. Which I'd had to do. And - you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they use the cane on the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Very seldom. Very seldom. There was only one girl in our class, she really was a terror. And - she used to get it I think - practically every week or every other week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't suppose with the girls you can remember any sort of gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Gangs? I don't think so, no. They used to play - sort of a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It's probably more with boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right. No, I don't think the girls had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your parents show interest in the schoolwork that you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I think they must have done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They asked you what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, because - and they'd - well they - at times I mean to say when I first started to - use an ink - a pen and ink, it was always the ink up here and - on the white pinafore, I'd always got spots on it, or else on my - if it was a white blouse -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would they go up to visit the school, and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not the - only if there were problems - I think, yes, only if there was problems would the parent - mothers go up to see the - teachers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So you don't remember your mother or father going up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No. No, I don't remember my mother having to go up for anything. I don't say I was always perfect but I don't think there was - I don't think there was anything problem like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But you feel they were keen on your getting on at school
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, they were interested in - yes, and wanted to know, I know we - wanted to know what we'd done the week and - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You then went on to the school at Streatham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There wasn't much difference between the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, not a lot of difference, no, 'cos that was a - fairly new school down - at Streatham. When - when I went back to school, that was 19 - well 1911 - when we went over to live at Strea
tham, I - we never - I never went to school until the started - until the September. You see, I had the whole of the summer at home. Year - wonderful year of - it was of weather too, I always remember that. Sun shine every day. But - then when I went back
 
to school my hus - my father had got a - a flat and he was a - away - quite a lot, and - my - uncle lived next door to the - schoolmaster - schoolmaster, attendance master you see, and he was able to arrange - that - I didn't go to school 'til ten o'clock
, but I had to be in by ten. Otherwise I was marked absent. And in that time - I was allowed to - put the house straight you see, do the - get the house - tidy and sort of make the beds. So that - that was a help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How old were you when you left then, Streatham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Left Streatham? What - oh that was when - I'd - started business then, and that was in - 1919 then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You left school in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No when I left - oh I left school - 19 - 14, was it when I - 14, yes, or 15. And then I went
 down to Brixton to Clarke's College - for a time, for a couple of years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of a place is that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Clarke's College was a - a com - they took - commercial work, shorthand and - secretarial job - business - you know, training I mean. A
nd - I did commercial - two - two sea - sessions in - I think - commercial. And then I went up for the - then I went up - again for - a year and - did shorthand and typewriting, learnt that you see. They've got - places - all over the place - I used to go
 to one at Brixton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So then you got a job of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 From there. Yes. That was - what 19 - 16 - no, before that I think. No, 1916 I suppose I started business didn't I. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Up 'til that time did you do any part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. Went st
raight - into - went into an Army bank then 'cos the war was on then you see. Well while we - one - I was going to say while we were at Clarke's College and supposed to be doing - lessons, and the war came on and we had to - sit - for oh - oh quite a week
 
or so or more and make - gas - gas - masks weren't they. And I thought it was awful, you know, paying money to - to be taught this and yet the - and then - to be made - asked to do that, but of course there was an urgency for it in the first world war for
 the gas you see, and - do them at - like that. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had no way in which you could earn a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. Not until I started - no, not until I started - business then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 This college, was there any kind of social life attached to the college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, no, you just went there - daily, you see, and - or perhaps you might - you - perhaps your - your - subjects may only be the afternoon, and - or - one week a - an afternoon, the next week all the mornings. Monday to Friday, not Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did you do the rest of the time when you were there, did you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh well, you used to have homework to do then you see. You had quite a lot of homework we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But there weren't any kind of clubs or anything like that at the college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\}Perhaps I'd better butt in here, Clarke's College - was a private fee paying school. It was not a college as - you know a college.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I was thinking of a kind of secretarial college.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} It w
as a - it was a secretarial college. It was started in a very small way, my own sister - one of my sister's went, one of them. They - they started in a small way, yes, and then they grew into a very big concern and I think it's still running. But it was n
e
arly a private school. It was not - I mean each - sort of branch - or place as - in - in Brixton, my sister went in Woolwich, they were entirely - self-contained affairs. There was - sort of no - inter - interchange with the other ones or anything of that
 sort you see. Just private -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 More - and Civil Service they used to - Civil Service, prepare for Civil Service exams and that. Both men and - the - men and the girls.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It was mixed was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Because some used to go in for - perhaps got in
to the War Office, or into the Admiralty you see through those - Civil Service exams. Or you might take up a - something from the tele - to - for the telephone exchange, anything like that, if you perhaps hadn't passed your exams - enough to go into - int
o a position to go into the - Civil Service - proper like, they might - they offered me once a - I hadn't quite passed for - for the Civil Service like I say, so - asked if I'd like to go to the - telephone exchange you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could you have a meal there for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What would you do about meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we used to - I used to take - sandwiches. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But there was a room where you could sit anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well only the classroom where you had - really, yes. And if I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Then you just had to clear out when your lesson was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. When - yes, or else - we might go - or have our lunch and then go out for a walk you see. To get the break. But there wasn't a proper - not a proper room or canteen or anything like that. Big old house wasn't it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So you would be fairly early on a pupil in this sense, it hadn't been going so very long at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think I had - two years there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I mean it hadn't been founded or started that long before you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't know, I think it had been - well established hadn't it. Mm. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\}
 It was fairly well established, I think it was established somewhere about - 05 or so, or round about the beginning of the century. Mm. Oh yes. They were quite - 
it was quite well known, and in fact, if you'd passed - passed through Clarke's College you'd usually be sure of a decent white collar. But of course it was fee paying and - the fees weren't ex - extraordinary much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh not so much then, no, I don't suppose really, no. But I didn't - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\}
 It depends I think on the - on the subjects you took. They did everything in - a sort of office - tuition, including French, they used to do French as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you do French then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I didn't do French. Geography and - dictation was mainly my - and - some English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Whose idea was it that you should go on to this college after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh my uncle's. Uncle wanted - you know, put me there and - and then as I say I took the commercial 
side, and then I went on - and took the - geog - took the - shorthand and typing. So I got into that, then I thought I'd go - get a job as a - that. I get - went into - an Army bank started off in an Army bank. So I didn't do the - I didn't do any of the 
- typing. Dropped all that. It's often like that isn't it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your father ever do any casual or part time sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. No. 'Cos - my father did sort of - decorate - the - inside the house but - not very often 'cos -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could you tell me who was in the household at Streatham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was my auntie and uncle, and my three cousins and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did your uncle do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He was - oh - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, business in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Surveyor. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 A professional then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well yes, you'd call - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they have any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well used to be the woman come and do the - washing on Mondays you see. And perhaps later on in the week she would come and - say Thursday or Fridays then clear up - for the weekend. But not - not a - a maid. Not actually a maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 A sort of daily you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
A day - yes, more or less, yes, or - or sometimes - some weeks would only be twice a week you see. 'Cos of course I had my jobs to do as well, yes, to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh peel the potatoes perhaps and - and perhaps I had to get up and - do the dine - the morning room where we had breakfast you see, tidy that up and dust that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How many rooms were there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well they had - there was a - a basem
ent, and that had - the - well scullery in those days it was called, the scullery, and the front room and the morning room. That's - those three rooms on the - in the basement, and then on the next floor there was - the - front room, dining room as they c
alled it, and the - lounge. And then - on the - floor above that was - two bedrooms and the bathroom and - toilet, separate you see, and then above that there was - two more - three more rooms. Two bedrooms and a sort of a box room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So it was a big place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, it was a - fairly big house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes, a long garden and the railway ran the - London Brighton railway ran at the bottom of the garden. So - as I say, we used to see the Queen - King and Queen - go down there in the summer when they went down to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portsmouth{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And many a time we've been at the bottom of the garden - and waved when the - train was coming back - coming to come down and Queen Mary and she used to - stand up and wave to us. Oh yes. And the - when 
the - that train came through for the - Royalty, all the coals were white - whitewashed. Yes. It's one of the things I - particularly remember - too for that. Yes, they were long gardens - flower beds and a lawn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They grew things, vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not many vegetables, I don't think, mainly flowers then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they have a gardener to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think we used to have a gardener some days. And then of course uncle used to do - quite a bit of - digging, tidying up etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't have a carriage or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No. Silk hat and - frock coat on Sundays of course for church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He was church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did he help at all in the house himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, not very much, might - he might ca
rry the - carry the things from - the dine - morning room out to the - scullery and - then probably go upstairs - and - spend the evening up in the - dining room you see. And the nice fire, for the winter time any rate. Oh we had a billiard table there to
o. Yes, because - I remember my father used to come - sometimes Saturday evenings, every other Saturday evening, and - we used to play billiards. I - used to play as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Your uncle wouldn't light the fires for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no. No, no. Auntie usually did that, or I did. Got those laid and - done those, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about looking after his children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, auntie did that mainly. 'Cos they were - I suppose fourteen or so then you see. One boy - the one cousin was - just - I think a year young
er than I and then the other one was two years and then the - the other boy and then the - girl, she was - three or four years younger than - the second boy you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They were all at local board schools were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Local schools, the - two boys w
ent to the Grammar school, and - I think Marjery must have gone to the - carried on school where I used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had to really rather more or less jobs in the house than you had at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I was older then you see of course so that naturall
y I would have to - gradually get more - do more and - you know, sort of be brought up in that way to sort of the - the idea sort of run - run - running a house I suppose really it used to be in those days. Training. To -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would your aunt sort of mend clothes or did she have them sent out to a dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, she used to make some too, 'cos she used to make me sometimes blouses and - that. I expect the boys things, they were bought. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But your uncle wouldn't mend the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no, no, uncle didn't mend the shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you say he working longer hours, was he back later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I don't think so. He was - you know a professional - I suppose - well I don't know, perhaps about in the morning 'til I suppose - perhaps half pa
st five in the evening. And then - sort of go - go - caught the train from Victoria back to Streatham and - got home I suppose about - seven I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He just simply expected to do less really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You would have your breakfast in this morning room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Morning room, down in the basement, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would you eat all the meals in there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, we had - all our meals there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So the meals were cooked in the kitchen and brought through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right, brought to the - morning room - as it was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was it all rather more sort of elaborate, the way the table was set?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh well the table was always set - yes, properly like, yes. Glasses and - knives and forks and that in the proper place, serviettes. We all had our own serviettes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you notice a difference in that way though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Living there, oh yes, it was a slightly - higher standard than what - we had of our - like with my father and mother, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about the way in which the meal was served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, all vegetable dishes were - on the table you see, vegetables were in dishes on the - on the table, they were all brought - into - onto the table, not served out outside. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was never a maid to wait on table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No. No, it's either - either auntie or I - myself got up and - did that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about the actual sort of food itself, how was that different? Could you tell me a typical day's meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I don't know really, I suppose we used to have s
tews and - very seldom had fish of course. But I suppose a joint and - or sausages and - mashed and greens like really. But - as I say, it was all - cooked in the kitchen and brought - through and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would she have meat most days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I thi
nk we had more joints you see which would last a couple of three days then you see. Oh yes, it's - it's - sort of was a - a slightly - better standard than - the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They didn't keep any livestock in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So they would buy eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You say they didn't really grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. Buy vegetables, yes, unless - people gave them round about you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about fruit, would they have fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not a lot really, of course you 
get the oranges, you'd have the oranges at Christmas time and that. Round about that season I mean, not - not necessarily only there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But they didn't have any apples trees or anything in the garden?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not fruit trees, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They didn't have tinned food as far as you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think so, no. No, very little finned - fruit in then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about the sort things that your aunt made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. That was always - bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did she do any bottling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not vegetables, I think - but she bottled fruit and made jam, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't recollect pickles. No, I don't actually rec - recollect pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. Never any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Any home made medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When you talked about what was actually eaten you were only talking about dinner I think, what about breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I think we had porridge and - bread and butter you see, or an egg, occa - occasionally, in the week. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Tea I think was mainly bread and butter and jam, for the children you see, and then uncle used to have a dinner when he came home. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 He had dinner by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Or with your aunt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, he used to 
have it mainly by himself, I mean she would sit there in the room or - some - in the wintertime I know he used to have it upstairs in the - dining room upstairs because we'd got the fire alight early you see, warmed up the room and - so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How much sort of contact did you have with him then? Did you have quite a lot of time talking to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, you could - oh yes, we went up in the eve - after - I'm - uncle had had his meal, then we went - the table was cleared and then we all went up there and
 - chatted or read books - read a book, or sometimes even played - billiards in the week. Or - or a friend might come in and - have a chat. Spend the evening with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you find - I wondered how much you managed to see of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not a lot, he came over - he probably come over every other week, on the Saturday evenings, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would this mean at that stage in your life really your uncle and aunt became more influential?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, definitely, yes, we - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 In what sort of ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well of course I - I - in a way, learnt - how to - I was only going to say exactly behave at table, but how to use the things at table you see and to - to set a table like that. And - those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you think it gave you different kind of ambitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well, I - I - sometimes looking back I was glad that I had - sort of lived with them and found out those things, and - picked up those things you see. Because - I do like things to be - nice, even today like I mean we're not - slipshod on the table now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But as far as the kind of things that were important in life, they had very much the same attitude as your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes That's right, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There wasn't any conflict that you felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh I don't think - I only once heard my father swear. And - I think he'd fallen over something in the dark. And that was very - well - well - wouldn't say tame really, 'cos it was only - blast, so 
I mean to say that was the only time I ever heard him swear - as I say, and - no, and - uncle and that - auntie and that never used - bad language and - naturally wouldn't - have us to - use it either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they entertain people more than your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
We - oh yes, yes, weekends, or Saturdays - mainly I mean, you'd have - friends come in. Sometimes Sundays - they'd come in to tea - too. In the summertime more especially really of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 This would be your friends you mean or their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well all together. Because their friends - I mean I was brought up - like with them in those years that their - their friends - we were all - all in the one family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were they older people, the same sort of age as your uncle and aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh - yes. Oh yes, yes. Mm. No I didn't have - personally I didn't have many friends like that. But - oh no, they were the - and they may have had children you see. And - brought the children along and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What would you do when there were these visitors, would there be a bit of a sing-song or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I think they usually mainly talked really - the - the older people talked, and we more or less went downstairs to the morning room and played - really with the younger 
ones. And - my cousin had a - a lot of soldiers you see and - we used to - you know, have games with those, the soldiers on the table or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But your uncle and aunt didn't play games when they had visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no, no. We didn't often play cards either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There wasn't anything like the singing round the harmonium?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, there wasn't - no, we didn't have that much with auntie. 'Cos we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, there was a piano there, yes. A
unt used to sing at times, we'd have a little musical evening occasionally but not very often. And - and aunties would sing. Uncle would sing his.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That would be other people who came in you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. Those evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Someone played sort of set pieces on the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
More or less, yes, that's right, yes. Un - uncle's favourite was the Admiral's Broom. Do you know that one? Bon Tromp was an Admiral brave and bold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about reading in the house, newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Library books.
 No, we didn't have many newspapers, because - see I wasn't there when the Titanic went down was I, no. So that - oh yes I was, 1912 wasn't it? Didn't I go to - 19 - 1912, yes. Yes, 'cos I remember we had to write an essay at school - about the Titanic an
d
 I didn't know anything 'cos I was not allowed to look at newspapers you see, until - almost - almost when I started business, and then - my uncle used to bring home the Evening Standard, and I'd take that up the next morning in - to read if I - wanted to
 you see. And of course all that news more or less was the same as what he got in the morning paper. So I used to take that. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they take any magazines, family magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I think the boys took possibly - the Boy Scout, is it the Boy Sco
ut was it one? And there was another they used to - Chum, was it, Chum was another one they used to have I think. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were your uncle and aunt keen readers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Uncle read a lot, yes. Auntie didn't read all that amount.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They wouldn't ever read to the family as a whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. But I know uncle used to - they used to get the library books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would they take you out on sort of family outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, we used to go out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of places would they go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh go up in - up to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 perhaps in the parks - or some - what my - not that museum, no, we used to go to - been to Horniman's museum that is at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Crystal{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Palace{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was is it, Horniman's, Sydenham way. Sydenham, yes, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They liked going to a museum or an art gallery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Holiday{\*\xmlclose} times like we'd - go up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they like going to concerts or theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, we used to go to the pictures. More then than - previous years, yes, we went to the pictures more, there was some - might be - sort of - 
if they're good pictures we might go every Saturday night. 'Cos - those - those days the picture was changed twice a week you see. So - you could go every - every - every week like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They were keen churchgoers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had to go to the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well it was more - yes, we - more into church then you see. Morning, and evening. My - my cousins - they were - started to be servers in the church you see. I don't think they were in the choir, no, I don't recollect them being i
n the choir but they were trained - took some training to be servers at the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you have family prayers in that home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, always grace at meals. With - auntie, ye
s. And you always asked if you could - you know - when you could leave the table. Sometimes you could, sometimes of course you - wait a little longer, if uncle hadn't finished or - auntie hadn't finished you see you had to wait a little longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they allow talking at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes, yes. That was more or less all - perhaps talking about school or talking about the boys at school and - cricket and things like that. That's where I got my - bit of enthusiasm for cricket. 'Cos the boys used to - m
y two cousins went to the grammar school you see, and a Saturday afternoons they'd perhaps go on the - playing field at - on Tooting Beck common and - play a - against another school or another class, and we used to go over and uncle - invariably - took t
he scores, or sometimes I'd take the book sometimes and - put the scores down you see. And - you know, sort of started an interest in it. I know we've seen some jolly good matches this last few Sundays on the - television.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So he was keen on cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. They - the boys played football but not a lot. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was he interested at all in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, but I don't think - I mean he and perhaps my father would have arguments. Friendly arguments, never - it was never - you know, di
sagreeable arguments, always friendly argument - arguments and that. But they didn't used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You don't remember what they were about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. They didn't used - uncle didn't used to go out to meetings - like - my father did, take a walk out - down the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you know what his political views were, your uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I - I suppose they were - Conservative I suppose, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about relationships with the neighbours there, would they come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. They wouldn't come in
 a lot, no, but we were all friendly with the - neighbours. And - very often the boys - the boys friends - school friends, they often used to come in. Perhaps Saturday afternoons and stay for the evening. And - they'd play games downstairs, they didn't pl
ay billiards much. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 If your aunt was ill would a neighbour come in and help ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I should think so but I - I can't recollect any time that auntie was ill. So - I rather think we're all gifted with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Any other relatives coming in, to give her a hand or anything, you don't remember that either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
No, I don't - I don't think it was really necessary really as far as I can see. The only - my uncle's mother, she lived in another road - down below, Mitcham Lane like down below, and sh
e used to come up - she was getting on in years of course - I mean in those days seventy to eighty I mean naturally was quite old, and she used to trot up - regularly Saturday afternoon - Saturday - mornings to - see us. And - then we'd walk to the end of
 the road with her and - see her off like, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Which side was your aunt and uncle on, your father's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
My father - auntie was my father's sister. Mm. She was the one of - she was the - they had six brothers, and just the one - female, and - they
 all died, the six brothers all died before they were fifty, and auntie lived 'til - eighty-one. Mm. Just the one you see who - happened to be the stronger - female sex was the stronger
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 We were talking about what kind of a district Thornton Heath was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I wonder whether you could give me a picture of the area where you lived in Streatham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well that was - Streatham was quite a - a - an uplift really as from Thornton Heath That's quite a nice suburb that was. And there were a l
ot of big houses there. I don't - oh well - Thrale Hall was at the back of us. That was a big place, who lived at Thrale Hall now? Mm. Now was it - oh. I know some - I can't remember who it was but I know there was somebody - big people lived there like. 
T
hrale Hall. Now I believe it's - did somebody say it was turned into flats or something now? Mm. Yes, there were a lot of - big houses - and all the roads where I lived leading up from the - Tooting Beck Common was the other end of the road, and all the h
o
uses round that were all - good - big sized houses and - more or less what you would say in those days were well to do, and those - running from the - from the - one side across the common up onto the High Street - they were all-well built houses too. The
 lower end, from sort of in - from the other end of the road where I - Mitcham Road, Mitcham Lane, down to - towards the station - that was the - and - and - that - that was the poor - well, you'd say the - working class - of - the area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They're detached houses you're talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Quite a lot of them were, yes, yes. Or semi-detached and - quite big you see, you might have - seven or eight rooms. But of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Nobody around where you were then kept a carriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think carriages - I think were about out then weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about keeping a motor car though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
There were - there would be - a few motor cars about. Yes, there would be a few motor cars. Of course the main transport was trams then wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did many of the people round you have living in domestic servants at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh some did, yes, yes. Not a lot, no, not a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 So it was kind of on the border really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Tradit - yes - transitional wasn't it, transitional. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't really at that time then have much to do with the working class district
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You weren't really aware of the different families there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Only when you had - had to walk down to the - station, you walked through that end down to go to Streatham - Common station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 On the other hand there wouldn't be anybody quite as sort of impressive as Sir William Trelawn for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think - I can't - there were one or two - yes. Yes, but I - I just can't think of their names at
 the moment, I don't - Actually I don't remember many carriage about that time - in London there might have been more would they because we were getting the - trams and that run - there were trams were running and that weren't they. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When you went down to the station you don't remember in the morning seeing these people driving up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. And we always walked down there. Always walked back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} Oh no, not - not at Mitcham you wouldn't. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But you did see that at Woolwich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\}
 Oh yes, and Eltham for instance you'd have people - driving down to the - station - to catch their trains, but then of course - again that was another - sort of - had been a stockbroker belt sort of thing, and was gradually a
ltering. But again - the houses there were big houses, and they were all Crown leases because it was all Crown land, consequently - it was only people who had - a pretty go do income that would take a leasehold house, you see. And - consequently they were
 quite - oh a lot of them quite wealthy, big - departmental store - shop - owners and - and that sort of thing, even -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Courtaulds lived out at New Eltham - out at Eltham didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} Yes. Was one of them - before my time there was even - 
dear old - Parnell. Because that's where he used to come courting Mrs - Mrs O'Shea. But that was much before my time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. But still that's what you got out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} You got that sort of thing you see, sort of secluded - country house that - has now become swamped with - suburbia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. And - and they were - big houses too. All along the Lee High Road, look at the big houses there were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} You see all along Streatham - yes, there were enormous big houses about. Big old tall houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. And I say, the same as Streatham there's some very big houses there. Turned into three or four flats now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} And - and the same, running into Streatham too you used to have - up - Brixton to Streatham was o
f course all the theatrical people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well from Brixton right up there. You see you'd have the - the house stand right back, and you'd have a - a two way - drive down to the - road. Then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} They had been carriage and pair houses sort of th
ing. You used to have a lot - around Streatham and - Brixton - of course were - were the big theatrical people. Marie Loyd and - all music hall people and all that sort of thing you see. And consequently of course you were sort of uppish - and yet you wer
e
 not, there was - there's the up and the down bits, you see, and - and gradually - tipping over into the down bits, put it that way. It - it's - it's - it's rather - it's rather peculiar because - it was an absolute transition - really. Because of course 
transport became much -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
And of course were were not quite old enough then really to - to notice it, you know, that even - today I mean we - really sort of don't remember it. Not change - you know. Certain things that you do. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I think you were going to tell me about the first job that you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, yes. Mm. Well of course as I said I'd taken two years - two years - down at Clarke's College. I think that was about eighteen months of - commercial. And then I went on to - as I say for the 
shorthand and typing. Well then I - applied round the various banks and they had no vacancies, or various banks and no - and - then I - applied to - an Army Bank, and I had a - and interview, and was taken on - at - Holt's - Army Agents they were, Holt's 
Bank, in Whitehall Place. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did you have to do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well no, not doing shorthand and typewriting, I never did any of that there. I was put on - addressing envelopes for - cheque books, sending out cheque books and that. And - writing u
p - onto the - or when the - end of the month - all the - monies went out, the Army Officers and that you see, their - allowances went out to their wive - wives and that - probably all by registered letter and that, I used to have to write those up you se
e
 in the post - in the post office book, I went down to the post office to be checked and then other books - other letters I had to write everything that was sent out you see, was - recorded - and - as I say I used to do the - send the cheque books out as 
well. Here there and everywhere. Abroad and otherwise.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That wasn't too routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh no, I - no, I had it - yes, 'cos sometimes as I say - you'd be waiting for a - you'd probably have - practically no work to do at all, and then suddenly you'd get
 a boat in or something from Egypt and you'd be - had - you might - two or three months of mail - have been held up and then of course you got - swamped with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of hours did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh long hours they were really, what, nine 'til - nine 'til six was it and - quite a lot of overtime we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you get a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Sundays - no, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  think it was half days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you work all of Saturday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Probably we would. Or we might get the Saturday afternoon and go in on the - for Sunday work, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had to work Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, throughout the war, first world war that was of course. Oh yes, we often had to do Sunday work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you get any holidays there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh - yes, you get your - bank holidays and that, and - and the - and the - fortnight holiday in the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You got a fortnight with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I suppose I did, yes. I expect I did with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What were you paid when you started there then? Do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh dear, dear, dear. I suppose about two pounds. It wouldn't be much more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did your aunt expect you to give most of that to her or did you keep it for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I had to give - yes, I had to give some up you see and I had to save some. And then some I
 could - you know, say - have the other for spending. Then save for the holidays and things like that too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How many people were there in this bank, did you work in a room by yourself or with a group of other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I was in a group - in the - in the bank you see, in the - you know, where the cashiers are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Sort of among the public almost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes, almost with the public like that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How did you get on with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 other people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I think pretty well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were they all doing different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, of course a lot of ladies were on ledgers. Others were letters you see, typists and that. And - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was it all women then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 In those days, yes, there were - a few men but of course they'd been - they'
d been called up, as their age group came along. And - oh yes, we were - finished up with practically - mostly women you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there a sort of manager who was in charge of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Of the department more or less yes. These what we called the
 bank manager, he was in charge of the - lower floor and then you'd have another floor with the - where - other - certain other correspondence was done, and - and he'd have - they'd have a man - they'd have a - their own - boss of their - that department 
you see. And then the - boss - was also there - Sir Veasey Holt, he was al - he - worked there as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you see anything of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Ay, oh yes, occasionally he'd come down, yes, yes, and - he'd always address you. He'd never pass you by as a - y
ou know - non - nondescript or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there any kind of life, did you all go out to lunch together or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we'd - we used to - pop out of - of - at our times you see, perhaps twelve to one or - one to two, ha
lf past twelve to half past one, had to work it round like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you go off to a caf\'e9?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm We were round at - went round into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Whitehall{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Lyons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 'Cos - when food got short you see, and Sundays - especially - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Lyons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} were only open for - War Office -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes, so - it was - only open then - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Lyons{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} was for those - three - work - working people you - Sunday workers. Otherwise there was another }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 one lower}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
 down the road that took the - ordinary public.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you get a chance to get to know these other people working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh yes, yes. Oh yes. Because my work was - you know, my - the work that I did you see - when - you know when you get a cheque book you've got to write out - you write out a slip, well half the time you couldn't read
 anybody's writing so of course I had to go round the various - ledger keepers to find out what their names were, their - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 hieroglyphics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  and that, and - oh yes, then of course when you - time when you - perhaps went up to wash your hands and that you - just got a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 cloakroom}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  where you were - chatted away perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But you weren't supposed to be chatting while you were actually in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 At work? Well it - not too - but not too much, we - you know, if you - all right if you kept quiet real
ly but of course some people have loud voices. And it depended, it depended on how much work you'd go to get through as to whether you could spare the time to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You had a definite amount you were supposed to get through each day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well not so
 much get through but of course as I say when you get a - when we had a - perhaps a - a big Egyptian mail in - well it might be a hundred or more - books had got to go out and get out quickly you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Was there somebody who would say the amount of work you must do today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, no. No. 'Cos - mm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 The ledger clerks, I mean sometimes they'd have heavy - heavy days - of - cheques - coming in, another day they might have quite a light - thing, well then of course that would - allow them to sort of pe
rhaps do some balancing in their books. But otherwise, if you get a heavy time all the time you don't get the chance, it takes you all your time to - get your cheques marked up and then from there they went into another room to be cancelled and suchlike a
n
d - it's quite a business. So that you might not get - start - posting your cheques until after dinner really, if - a man gets some heavy stuff to get through. But - but as I say according to the - how the - stuff came - posts came in, whether the ships h
ad been sunk and - things like that, all - added up to - to the - a - a certain amount of days works and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would they used the telephone at all in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Pardon? Did they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did they use the telephone at all at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh the telephone was there, yes, because you probably had to - call from one office to another, for something, they prob -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 In the same building you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. Yes. We were off of the War Office. I remember the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What about typewriters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh type - the typewriting was in a - in another department you see. That was right at the top, the typewriting department. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You wouldn't use adding machines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I don't think adding machines - not at first, they might have come in a bit lat
er on. But - after - yes, I saw the - blinds come down when - Kitchener was drowned. I was in - Whitehall then. Well they were opposite you see and the word came in and - we heard that, and also I was in - Whitehall when the - at the first - burial of the
 unknown soldier, in - 1918 wasn't it, November the eleventh 1918. Mm. Oh 19 was it, war finished then didn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you really enjoy that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, yes, I certainly did. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I was there for five years
. Yes. And then of course the war was over and then I think they got rid of - they began to get - rid of the - lady staff, female staff you see. I was not the first to go but - after some - oh it was nearly a twelve month after they started - going down t
hat - you felt - your name might be on the next list to - or next time to come along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There was a National Union of Clerks at that time, you didn't belong to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I didn't - no. I don't - had that - I don't think that had started had it the
 Oh - well, oh well, no, I didn't belong - we didn't belong to anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There wasn't any kind of consciousness of trade }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 unionism}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there ever any conflicts about work conditions and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not that I remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Do you think working sort of changed your attitude really to life in any particular ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I can't say that it did then. Don't recollect - like anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Have you done any other kind of work since then, which isn't clerical work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes. Well for - leaving - following - when I was leave - left the - left the bank - I - I'd left my aunt then and I was in digs with my sister. So of course I had to - I hadn't - couldn't afford to be out of work for long.
 And a friend - one of the men at the bank - said his sister had got - a butchers shop in Woolwich, and - knowing - him knowing my position really - he asked if I'd like to - go down there, and see them. And I was at - living at Peckham then. So - oh I sa
i
d, well I'll - I'll go down and see them and they were very nice people and - I was with them, I started and I was with them for ten years. And then - I left there and then I went to another butchers shop and I was with them for ten years. Then I left to 
g
et married. So that was quite an in - quite an interesting life. It's only twice I - you know the flats they have in the - butchers shop, do you know the old flaps they pull up - a flap out - flap - flap out of the - off the floor you know, well I - twice
 I fell down that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Lucky escapes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes they were really. First time I went down I - well of course the boy - the lad - pulled it up you see - they should have put chains round before he - pulled the flap up. And - I was serving and somebody w
anted some liver, you know, big ox liver, I'd got fresh ox liver on a board, I used to cut it - do that Saturday mornings you see, liver was my - so I did that, and I picked this liver up and turned round and I went down the - with the liver as well. But 
a
fter that one - following that I had to have a fortnight at home because I - real - really did - shake me up and I sort of hurt my back. And I got over that. And some years after that I was - as I say, going round - well I'd got a flit tin, you know, goin
g
 round like this round the - round the walls like this before we started, got the it was in the summertime before the fellows got the meat up out of - to put in the window. And I was going round like this, you see, fellow comes along, opens it up you see 
a
nd of course I go down. Yes, I can laugh about it now. That - shook me up and bruised me but - oh I - I - and - he'll tell you about the cuts I used to have, even before we were married, he used to come down, pick up and see what pieces there were to pick
 up or take home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} I often used to say I should have a - I should have a bagful of pieces and no wife.</}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid869172 subject2>}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I wasn't married then, we weren't married - I wasn't married then was I
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you prefer the work in the shop, was that more enjoyable would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well it was more open. It - it was - you know, fresh air sort of - fresh air and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You mean you got out doing deliveries and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no, no, well of course it was an open door, cold and all that. And I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 
travelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
 - from - Clapham to Woolwich - for three years I think and then I moved down to Woolwich. You see, and then - then from Woolwich I went travelling around again, up to their various shops. This was only the one shop - down in Woolwich. Althoug
h they had brothers and he had brothers that had got shops, but the other one was a - big firm, had got shops all over the place, round {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and that. So I went to - Woolwich, I went to the - oh I went to the one at New Cut? You know the New Cut in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Waterloo{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
? The Cut. Went to one there, and then I was at - one at - Peckham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 These were all family businesses were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That was a fam - sort of family business, yes, yes, that one was. And - finished up at Woolwich didn't I. In the shop down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you find the life in the office was being rather stuffy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Yes, yes. Mm. I was - and when I was - when I was - went down into the - into the shops you see, well although I was standing all the week really, and we never had a chair - very seldo
m sat down or anything, but - I used to go out walking every weekend, every Sunday rather I mean, what I call weekend, walking. Used to go out round rambles on the - round - we - railway rambles.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Railway rambles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. S.P.B. Mays used to do one
 didn't he, who was the other one that did them? I forget his name now. Any rate, we used to get on - go off the train somewhere or other and - of course they were - got - were reasonable you see. And then we used to break away from them and go - spend ou
r Sunday somewhere or other walking, and then join them on the train come - to come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It was a weekend ramble was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, only the one day. Sunday. Sometimes they had {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midnight{\*\xmlclose} - night rambles and carried on the next day, but - I didn't go on any of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} Yes, and - the Southern railway used to do them be - before the last war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Night Rambles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} No, they used to do - every Sunday, they'd have a special train - would go off on rambles you see, it was organised by a
 man, I forget his name now but he founded the Ramblers Association. Used to - buy - buy your ticket you see and on the train you were given - a - a sort of programme, they used to divide up into - three or four different walks. Well we used to go out wit
h
 this man - and he was a devil for walking, it used to be a case - you had to walk with a stop - stop watch, and if you weren't at the sort of last oak at two minutes to twelve there was a blast on the whistle and you had to chase like mad to get to the n
e
xt point. And - there'd be sometimes - oh perhaps - a hundred of more people in the party, straggled out all across the paths for miles sort of things. Well we used to go out with them and - get a programme, see where they were going and then - when we go
t
 to the destination, we'd know where the parties were going, we'd buzz off on our own you see. Or we used to perhaps - go - follow a party by letting them get about - half an hour ahead of us so that we could just see them across country, and we used to w
ander round on our own, and then join up - to come back on the special special train - at night. Sometimes they used to have - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midnight{\*\xmlclose} rambles - let's see, we used to do one - used to do one down in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Devon{\*\xmlclose} to - see the dawn. But I don't think we ever did se
e the sun rise, because it was always a cloudy night. But they'd ramble and then - they'd - break off, there was a special train back somewhere about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning you see. Or if you wished you could go off on another - period of rambling an
d come back and - pick up another special train. They were very very reasonable, they only used to cost us about - half a crown or I suppose the dearest one was about five bob. I think the cheapest one now is about twenty-five bob. So that - I - I think t
hey're still running from Swanley but - we'd had some - wonderful trips all over southern England.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When did you start doing that though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 \{Mr V.\} Oh - about 19 - in the 1930's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I did it before you - I started before I'd met you didn't I. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You wouldn't have been doing that in the war though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not in the 1918 war, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 When you were still in the bank what sort of entertainments did you manage to find at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well there was pictures, I know I went - you kn
ow, you - if by any chance I'd - you got your certain work done or so much done you couldn't get on I - I might ask if I could get off early, which meant about half past five. I remember once I - I - very seldom got off early but I know once I went off ea
r
ly, I wanted to go to the pictures at - Clapham Common. And I went - went to the pictures. The next morning when I went to the office, what are you doing here? You should be down at Folkestone, I had to go to Folkestone on a court martial and - you know, 
got chased like that. I went down to - on a court martial to - I was down there for what - first two days, then I went - came back and then - I had about another five days down at Folkestone there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You said you went to the Old Vic too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, I used to - oh yes, used to go to the Old Vic to see things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you go away for any holidays in that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes. I used to go with the - holiday fellowship. There again they were rambling you see, they did a lot of rambling and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That's when you were in the bank you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 That would be somewhere in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Pardon? Yes, yes, I never went abroad with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What sort of places would you go to with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I started up - I start
ed down at Swanage the first one. Wait a minute though, I - wait a minute, was it as early as that. No, it wouldn't have been would it, 'cos I was at the bank 'til 1921. I don't think I started with the rambling - ramblers - association 'til about 1924, 5
.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Had you always been quite keen on walking though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, I always - yes, I did like walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you find there were other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Like your cousins who liked walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. Not so much, no, they didn't really, they h
ad bicycles and that, I couldn't get a - I couldn't sit a bicycle, I could never sit a bicycle. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Where do you think you got the enthusiasm for walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 I don't know. Oh probably 'cos I had to walk - when I was down - going down to Clarke's Co
llege I had to walk down there every day. From - Streatham you see down to Clarke's College. Down to Brixton. I suppose that was three miles wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there any other sports that you took part in at that time when you were in the bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No. I didn't have time for - no, we really didn't have much time for those things really. No, I was not a tennis pan - at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You were still following cricket though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh I might have followed cricket then, yes. Or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  I - you know, if were out a walk and I saw a cricket match I'd stop and - have - for - quarter of an hour or so perhaps and watch them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were you still going to church on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not so much then, no. No. No, I certainly didn't go so much then. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You'd go on a walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Yes. Yes. I'd find it was - really more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 beneficial}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  to be out and - out in the fresh air.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You didn't start becoming interested in politics yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you sort of get to meet new people through work or any way like that, or did you not feel that you did meet many new people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Well I - I - what do you mean, during the - days of the shop? Or the - bank? Not a lot really, no. Because it was a sort of a mad scramble - in those days I mean it was in the war wasn
't it, and - it got pretty hot then - where - getting home or you might get - held up - for hours. And then of course you'd got to - scramble to get home when the - all clear had gone. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 There weren't any people that you worked with in the bank that became special friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No. No, I never made any - had no - never had a special friend in the bank. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You can't think of anything at that time at the bank about your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Sort of we're at home, as I say really, and if there was 
a pic - picture I wanted to see I'd go to the pictures. More or less for relaxation. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 It was a very quiet sort of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Quiet life, yes, well of course as I say we were so - working up to the hilt - perhaps week after week you see, and 
just then you might just get a sudden break, and - so we - perhaps got home then and - managed to get home early and - go to the pictures - Saturday afternoon or evening like really. Then again you never knew when the - bombs were coming down. Zeps.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were there kind of parties at the bank then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, we didn't - we didn't go in for parties like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 One sometimes gets a picture of the war as a time when people were working very hard, but then you know there was sort of a lot }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 of fun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 same}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Mm. No, in fact - no, we didn't - just the hard work. That's right, hard work all graft all the time. I think I was born on a Saturday wasn't? Born on a Saturday, and - it's always - I've often thought of it. Is it Saturday's child is lovi
ng and giving? No, Friday's child is loving and giving, Saturday's child has to work for its living, and I thought to myself, it's very true, very true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Were you expected to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh yes, yes, definitely. Right up 'til the - oh well, yes - we had to be in and - bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. When I was with auntie, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Even when you were in the bank you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no, wait a minute, what - what time am I talking about. 1915, yes. 1916 to 21 I was in the bank, and I was with au
ntie 'til 1919 wasn't I. Yes. Well up 'til - while I was with auntie I was still a sort of a - bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the week, and Saturdays I would be - you know, a bit later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Would she want to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm. Yes. Yes, I got caught o
nce 'cos I'd written a letter to a boy. I'd got it in a book you see and of course you're not supposed to take books to - books out with you. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not supposed to take books out with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, I - no, I was - brought up to - to work, not to have - not to have books to read, not when I was out. When I was supposed to work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You mean you took a book to read at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Well I suppose I - I - yes. I don't know but - no, it was - I suppose auntie's idea. Any rate, I'd written this letter you 
see and tucked it in the book you see just as I was going out. She called me back for something and - oh dear me. So of course when uncle came home I - had to go be - to aunt before uncle. Wanted to know who he was and what he was and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 They were annoyed because they didn't know who it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
His - yes. Yes, because - no, yes, because - your - their idea - their idea was that - a man should be - able to - before you thought of - going out with boys or anything you were to find somebody whos
e able to keep you, you know. But that's not to, you know, play about like some do, but if you're going to have a - meet a young man well you've got to be - true to him. Sort of first one I suppose and there we are. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 Victorians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Is that one reason why you decided to move out into digs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Could I just ask you what your brothers and sisters did for jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 What did - my sister started in a - drapers and - linen shops, yes, she was older than I. She would be five years older t
han I. Yes, Fred was - wait a minute same as - same as father - heating engineer. Yes, my brother Bob, the youngest one he was the same. And Jim was in the - draughtsman, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 And your older sister married, what was her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 She didn't marry, did any other the others marry somebody who had a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
My - brother - my twin brother, the - Fred - I don't know whether - 'cos he married Florrie didn't he. Not a - not a special job. She'd probably go out and help somebody do - so
me work for somebody. You know, more like a home help, as a home help. When she was younger. And my other brother, the - Bob, his wife - oh she used to be in Eldorade didn't she. After - well she was - she was - she was also - she was a - sort of a maid, 
wasn't she, a maid - at - crystal Palace way wasn't it, big houses like that, yes, that's right. And more - a maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 She worked for Eldorado, that's the ice cream shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 After. Ice cream people, yes, in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 As a sort of shop assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 No, no. No, at the ice cream firm. Making ice creams - in - in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 You wouldn't know what kind of job she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 had in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh she made all the - special - special ice creams. No. Moulds and that. Yes. She'd say ice cream but they used 
to make them. Crinoline ladies you know, with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 crinoline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
 ladies and that. Oh it was, beautiful stuff it used to be. She made a - the golden wedding wasn't it? And she made a - a cake for the passing out at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Sandhurst{\*\xmlclose} - once when she did - was doing that. Now
 my brother used - didn't - didn't they used to make wine? They started it didn't they, making some wine. Bob. Didn't he? A little - some - wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you see much of them once you'd moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Not a lot, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Did you miss them a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
Oh I did miss them, yes. Yes. But my brother - my - Fred and I are twins you see, although we're not identical - and we may have been miles apart, yet things have happened - when we've known about it. Mm. He was at Faversham in the first world war and 
I was living at Streatham, and we both went to the dentist for the first time on the same day, and - we wrote - sort of - he wrote and told me after - wards that - a week or two afterwards, and - I - as I say that was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1972245\charrsid731478 strange}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478  thing. And then years after 
that - I'd had - already had my teeth extracted, but - all my jaws did ache one day, for a couple of days, oh they did ache and I said to - my husband, I said, oh I - something's happening, I says, I should think Fred's - Fred's not well or something, but
 any rate - he - wrote and said he'd - had all his teeth out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11744959 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 But he'd gone off to another house so that time you didn't see much of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10318493 AV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 Oh no. No. When he first got married I saw - quite a bit of him because - he was living at - Upper Nor - no
 - no - South Nor - Sels - oh where was it, South Norwood - Thornton Heath, South Norwood was it South Norwood. And I - I was living at Woolwich then and I - often used to go over. Especially when they had - like the first two, his first two children - I 
was over there quite a lot. Then of course they moved away a bit - further so - I gradually - suppose as the children got older then I - they're now married with their own family.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-461\li461\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11744959 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6051918\charrsid731478 
